From 85f456fdfe8b53dfafdc78dd25583b2da34b4ea0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: quivent <quivent@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Wed, 8 Apr 2026 14:05:46 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] feat(memory): recurrent-state snapshot/restore for DeltaNet
 rollback

Add a snapshot/restore API for the llama_memory_recurrent conv_state and
rnn_state tensors used by Qwen3-Next and other hybrid DeltaNet models.
Speculative decoding can now capture the recurrent state before drafting,
and cheaply restore it on rejection without re-running a full forward pass.

The snapshot copies only the small per-layer recurrent tensors (KB/layer)
plus cell metadata; KV-cache rollback for attention layers in hybrid
models is handled separately via the existing llama_memory_seq_rm path.

Public API in include/llama.h:
  llama_memory_snapshot_recurrent(ctx, out_handle)
  llama_memory_restore_recurrent(ctx, handle)
  llama_memory_release_snapshot(handle)
  llama_memory_snapshot_size(handle)

A TODO(split-rec) marker is left in src/models/qwen3next.cpp describing
the follow-up work to split the GDN recurrence into T=1 steps while
keeping the surrounding matmuls batched at T=N, mirroring the MLX
reference in delta_net_rollback.py.
